vim-rails - a plugin for the text editor Vim

Should you care if you are not a Vim user?

John McPhee and Kedit
http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2013/01/14/structure

Check out other editors

Candy Crush Saga
=================

vimscript sucks
http://learnvimscriptthehardway.stevelosh.com/
a lot of plugins overwrite default behavior / keybindings in scary ways
Tim Pope!
https://github.com/tpope/vim-rails
https://github.com/tpope/vim-rake


installation:
use pathogen!
https://github.com/tpope/vim-pathogen
mkdir -p ~/.vim/autoload ~/.vim/bundle && \
curl -LSso ~/.vim/autoload/pathogen.vim https://tpo.pe/pathogen.vim

echo 'execute pathogen#infect()
syntax on
filetype plugin indent on' >>~/.vimrc

then...
cd ~/.vim/bundle
git clone git://github.com/tpope/vim-rails.git
git clone git://github.com/tpope/vim-bundler.git
vim 
:Helptags
:help rails-introduction
:help rails-vim-integration

gf - finds the file that defines the class

:A ("alternate") - usually the test
:R ("related") - varies, may depend on location within file
from models/user.rb
:A -> test/models/user_test.rb

:E ("edit") - 
:E(thing)

plus 4 more forms
:S ("split")
:V ("vertical split")
:T ("tab")
:D ("destructive"?)

:Rails
===============
take-away:
Your tools may influence how you design 
  DHH uses TextMate.
  a vim user might have made either a more flat dir structure,
  or turned it "inside-out"
Script your editor
go slow with customization
Steal!
Don't get trapped in a closed source editor


